ðŸ“Š ECR (Elastic Container Registry): 

its a container registry similar to Dockerhub,it is used to store the Docker images.
if there is Elastic in the name then the service is highly scalable and available in nature .


Create an ECR registry with aws cli :
1. aws configure
2. Create an ECR Repository:
 aws ecr create-repository --repository-name my-app --region us-east-1
3. Authenticate Docker with ECR:
  aws ecr get-login-password --region us-east-1 \
| docker login --username AWS --password-stdin 123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com
4. docker build -t my-app .
5. Tag Your Image for ECR:
  docker tag my-app:latest 123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:latest
6. Push the Image to ECR:
 docker push 123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:latest
7. Pull the Image from ECR (for ECS/EKS):
 docker pull 123456789012.dkr.ecr.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/my-app:latest
8. 
